---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Projects">
  <h1>Projects</h1>
  <p class="meta">Every finished thing links back to the devlog entries that built it.</p>

  <div class="card">
    <h3><a href="/projects/quest-planner/">Quest Planner</a> <span class="badge growing">in build</span></h3>
    <p>Gamified Franklin-style planner for iOS. Local-first, one-time purchase, no subscription.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3><a href="/projects/diginodes/">DigiNodes</a> <span class="badge growing">re-skin</span></h3>
    <p>Digital card game built on an existing, proven HTML engine. Will be playable at <a href="/play/">/play/</a>.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3><a href="/projects/kaiju-defense/">Kaiju Defense</a> <span class="badge growing">in build</span></h3>
    <p>Modern spiritual successor to SNES Metal Marines: asymmetric island defense against a growing alien hive. Free to play, donation-supported.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3><a href="https://madbobbitt.github.io/familyconvoy/">Family Convoy</a> <span class="badge evergreen">evergreen</span></h3>
    <p>A Mille Bornes variant: race 1,000 miles to Wallyworld. Playable now. Same engine DigiNodes is re-skinning. (looks better on mobile)</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3>WARDEN <span class="badge seed">in design</span></h3>
    <p>Near-future facility sim: you are the AI, and you can only shape the environment, never the people.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h3>Laborer <span class="badge seed">in design</span></h3>
    <p>Far-future isometric survival with a "lit SNES" look: retro pixels, real-time light.</p>
  </div>
</Base>
